<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>纽约时报 &amp;gt; 美国 &amp;gt; 政治</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/spotlight/on-politics</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 22 Jun 2026 20:06:37 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>纽约会进一步左倾吗？这是周二初选的预览。</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/22/us/politics/new-york-primaries-preview.html</link><description>该市充满戏剧性、高支出的初选将提供进步势头和市长佐兰·马姆达尼影响力的线索。</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Jun 2026 20:06:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/22/us/politics/new-york-primaries-preview.html</guid></item><item><title>特朗普在佐治亚州的人能打败乔恩·奥索夫吗？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/us/politics/ossoff-collins-georgia-senate.html</link><description>众议员迈克·柯林斯 (Mike Collins) 在一场艰苦的共和党初选中获胜，意味着参议院的一场重大对决现已确定。</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 17:34:50 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/us/politics/ossoff-collins-georgia-senate.html</guid></item><item><title>阿拉巴马州和佐治亚州决选将对特朗普明天的影响力进行新的考验</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/15/us/politics/georgia-alabama-runoff-primary-elections-trump.html</link><description>桃州以及阿拉巴马州将对特朗普的影响力进行新的考验。</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 21:30:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/15/us/politics/georgia-alabama-runoff-primary-elections-trump.html</guid></item><item><title>特朗普随意的中期领导让共和党陷入困境</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/us/politics/trump-midterms-republicans.html</link><description>在春季充满了 MAGA 初选胜利和重新划分选区的成果之后，总统和他的政党在 6 月份的开局并不顺利。</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 21:06:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/us/politics/trump-midterms-republicans.html</guid></item><item><title>民主党人试图在中期选举中摆脱对拉丁裔的“文化迎合”</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/us/politics/latino-voters-democrats-elections.html</link><description>该党正在拼命地试图赢回关键摇摆群体中的一些选民。</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 23:42:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/us/politics/latino-voters-democrats-elections.html</guid></item><item><title>国会的控制权可以贯穿缅因州北部吗？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/us/politics/maine-second-district.html</link><description>该州广阔的农村地区构成了摇摆不定的第二国会选区，在 11 月份将发挥重要作用。</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 15:45:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/us/politics/maine-second-district.html</guid></item><item><title>关于缅因州和南卡罗来纳州初选的三个问题</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/08/us/politics/maine-south-carolina-primaries.html</link><description>格雷厄姆·普拉特纳和林赛·格雷厄姆都希望能够轻松取得重大胜利。</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 22:56:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/08/us/politics/maine-south-carolina-primaries.html</guid></item><item><title>在格雷厄姆·普拉特纳的争议中，缅因州参议院竞选下一步将走向何方？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/05/us/politics/maine-senate-graham-platner-democrats.html</link><description>关于格雷厄姆·普拉特纳的新披露让民主党人感到焦虑。</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 21:51:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/05/us/politics/maine-senate-graham-platner-democrats.html</guid></item><item><title>周二加州、爱荷华州和其他地方的大型初选的六个问题</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/03/us/politics/primaries-california-iowa-questions.html</link><description>谁将管理加州？民主党能赢得爱荷华州吗？这就是发生的事情，以及接下来可能发生的事情。</description><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 17:38:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/03/us/politics/primaries-california-iowa-questions.html</guid></item><item><title>预览加州初选和高风险的州长竞选</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/us/politics/california-primary-elections-governor-preview.html</link><description>这个深蓝色州的初选将显示选民对现状有多么愤怒。</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 15:15:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/us/politics/california-primary-elections-governor-preview.html</guid></item></channel></rss>